I have another pretty
heavy usually question,

00:36:46.805 --> 00:36:49.241 align:middle line:84%
but I'm sure you're going
to bring light to it.

00:36:49.241 --> 00:36:51.410 align:middle line:90%
Truths, what is true?

00:36:51.410 --> 00:36:54.513 align:middle line:84%
>> van der Vliet: Ooh,
ooh, ooh, ah, ah, ah.

00:36:54.513 --> 00:36:59.685 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think that
truth is about knowing

00:36:59.685 --> 00:37:03.088 align:middle line:84%
and about being right,
which is from our mind.

00:37:03.088 --> 00:37:06.191 align:middle line:84%
My general idea is
that you don't have

00:37:06.191 --> 00:37:09.528 align:middle line:84%
to believe everything
your mind produces.

00:37:09.528 --> 00:37:13.665 align:middle line:84%
And if you do life becomes,
life becomes a lighter.

00:37:13.665 --> 00:37:15.600 align:middle line:90%
Truth is a personal thing.

00:37:15.600 --> 00:37:17.969 align:middle line:84%
And so for me I do this
yoga every morning.

00:37:17.969 --> 00:37:19.071 align:middle line:90%
This is my truth.

00:37:19.071 --> 00:37:21.173 align:middle line:90%
It works for me.

00:37:21.173 --> 00:37:26.578 align:middle line:84%
And so it works for me, but
truth is a personal thing.

00:37:26.578 --> 00:37:28.680 align:middle line:90%
So, it's not something that--

00:37:28.680 --> 00:37:34.753 align:middle line:84%
I cannot force my truths up onto
you I think you say in English.

00:37:34.753 --> 00:37:37.989 align:middle line:84%
And because there's my truth
and there's your truth.

00:37:37.989 --> 00:37:40.225 align:middle line:84%
And so truth basically
doesn't exist.

00:37:40.225 --> 00:37:41.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Um hmm.

00:37:41.560 --> 00:37:42.961 align:middle line:84%
>> van der Vliet: Truth is
what the average idiot thinks--

00:37:42.961 --> 00:37:44.029 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Um hmm.

00:37:44.029 --> 00:37:45.430 align:middle line:84%
>> van der Vliet: Or
believes to be true.

00:37:45.430 --> 00:37:49.935 align:middle line:84%
And so basically this is blue,
but if 51 percent of the people

00:37:49.935 --> 00:37:53.638 align:middle line:84%
in the world would say no,
this is green I would be wrong.

00:37:53.638 --> 00:37:54.639 align:middle line:90%
So, truth is relative.

00:37:54.639 --> 00:37:56.742 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't exist.

00:37:56.742 --> 00:37:58.010 align:middle line:90%
And then on the other hand

00:37:58.010 --> 00:37:59.811 align:middle line:84%
and so everybody has
their personal truth.

00:37:59.811 --> 00:38:00.812 align:middle line:90%
Truth doesn't exist.

00:38:00.812 --> 00:38:02.581 align:middle line:90%
This is my point of view.

00:38:02.581 --> 00:38:07.352 align:middle line:84%
And then some, somebody could
say it's more philosophical.

00:38:07.352 --> 00:38:11.523 align:middle line:84%
But-- well love is the truth,
you know and fear isn't.

00:38:11.523 --> 00:38:13.959 align:middle line:84%
Yeah in the philosophical
way I could say okay,

00:38:13.959 --> 00:38:16.828 align:middle line:84%
okay if there is a higher
truth then you could say

00:38:16.828 --> 00:38:19.531 align:middle line:90%
that love is the higher truth.

00:38:19.531 --> 00:38:20.665 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Mmm.

00:38:20.665 --> 00:38:21.967 align:middle line:84%
>> van der Vliet: You
know because this is--

00:38:21.967 --> 00:38:25.370 align:middle line:84%
when I have a problem with
something or a challenge I--

00:38:25.370 --> 00:38:29.141 align:middle line:84%
often I'll ask myself
okay what is my problem

00:38:29.141 --> 00:38:31.109 align:middle line:90%
and what would love decide.

00:38:31.109 --> 00:38:35.447 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes your love
decision is quite tough

